---
import LegalLayout from '../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---
<LegalLayout
  lang="en"
  title="Privacy Policy — Michael Boiman"
  description="Privacy information for this website and the AI chat assistant."
>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: June 2026</p>

  <p class="legal-muted">
    This is an English courtesy translation. The
    <a href="/de/datenschutz">German version</a> is legally authoritative.
  </p>

  <p>
    This website (<strong>mboiman.github.io</strong>) is a personal CV site with an
    optional AI chat assistant. Personal data is processed only to the minimal extent
    described below. There is <strong>no tracking, no advertising and no analytics
    cookies</strong>.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Controller</h2>
  <address>
    Michael Boiman<br />
    Zum Gottschalkhof 2<br />
    60594 Frankfurt am Main, Germany<br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:mboiman@gmail.com">mboiman@gmail.com</a>
  </address>

  <h2>2. Visiting the website (hosting)</h2>
  <p>
    The site is served as a static page via <strong>GitHub Pages</strong> (GitHub,
    Inc., 88 Colin P. Kelly Jr. Street, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA). When you visit,
    GitHub processes technically necessary access data (including IP address, date and
    time, the resource requested, amount of data transferred, browser type) in order
    to deliver the page and keep operation secure and stable. The legal basis is
    Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in secure, functional provision).
  </p>

  <h2>3. AI chat assistant</h2>
  <p>
    The site offers an optional chat assistant. Use is voluntary — your input is only
    processed if you send a message yourself.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Processing of messages:</strong> Your input is sent to the agent
      endpoint <em>mboiman.bks-lab.com</em> and forwarded to the AI service
      <strong>Anthropic</strong> (Anthropic PBC, San Francisco, USA — "Claude") to
      generate a reply. Transport runs through <strong>Cloudflare</strong>
      (Cloudflare, Inc., USA), which processes technical connection data (including IP
      address) to protect the service against abuse and overload.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Storage of the conversation:</strong>
      <strong>We do not store the conversation.</strong> The conversation history is held
      only transiently in memory for the duration of the session and is lost on restart
      or inactivity. Our operational logs record at most the length of a message, never
      its content.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Local browser storage:</strong> To operate the chat, a technical session
      identifier is stored in your browser's local storage so a conversation can
      continue across a page reload. This storage is technically necessary
      (§ 25(2) no. 2 TTDSG) and is not used for tracking. No analytics or advertising
      cookies are set.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Contact and appointment requests:</strong> Only if you actively make a
      request and provide details such as your name and email or phone number are
      these stored in order to process your request.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The legal basis for operating the chat is Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest
    in answering questions about me and my work); for transmitting contact details as
    part of a request, Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (pre-contractual steps) or Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR
    (consent by sending).
  </p>
  <p class="legal-muted">
    Note: Please do not enter personal, confidential or special categories of
    personal data (e.g. health, religious or political data) into the chat.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Recipients and transfers to third countries</h2>
  <p>
    Within the scope described, data is transferred to the following services based in
    the USA: <strong>GitHub</strong> (hosting), <strong>Cloudflare</strong> (transport
    and protection of the chat) and <strong>Anthropic</strong> (AI responses). Transfer
    takes place on the basis of the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (where the
    respective company is certified) or the EU Standard Contractual Clauses pursuant to
    Art. 46 GDPR. No data is passed on to any other third parties.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Retention period</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Chat history:</strong> transient, not stored permanently (see section 3).</li>
    <li>
      <strong>Contact and appointment requests:</strong> until your request has been
      conclusively handled; deleted thereafter unless statutory retention obligations
      apply.
    </li>
    <li><strong>Server access data from hosting:</strong> as determined by GitHub.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    You have the right to access (Art. 15), rectification (Art. 16), erasure (Art. 17),
    restriction of processing (Art. 18), data portability (Art. 20) and the right to
    object to processing based on legitimate interests (Art. 21 GDPR). You may withdraw
    any consent given at any time with effect for the future (Art. 7(3) GDPR). An
    informal message to
    <a href="mailto:mboiman@gmail.com">mboiman@gmail.com</a> is sufficient.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Right to lodge a complaint</h2>
  <p>
    You have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory
    authority — e.g. the Hessian Commissioner for Data Protection and Freedom of
    Information, Postfach 3163, 65021 Wiesbaden, Germany.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    This privacy policy will be updated whenever the service or the legal framework
    changes.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
